w.wikidata.org/wiki/Wikidata:Lexicographical_data/Documentation/Languages/ru/modeling\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n- All nouns are expected to have grammatical gender (P5185) with one or more of masculine (Q499327), feminine (Q1775415) and neuter (Q1775461).\n- Every noun is expected to have has characteristic (P1552) animate (Q51927507) or inanimate (Q51927539).\n- All nouns are expected to have a paradigm class (P5911) which must be either of 1st declension in Russian (Q66327367), 2nd declension in Russian (Q66689134), or 3rd declension in Russian (Q66689140)\n\n- plus a specific Zaliznyak index, e.g. class\n...\n1c in Zaliznyak (Q66606177\n...\n- Some nouns that only have a subset of\n...\ninstance of (P31))\n...\nsingulare tantum (Q604984) or plurale tantum (Q138246)\n...\n#### Grammatical features\n...\n### Forms: grammatical features\n...\nQ348\n...\n78), comparative (Q14169499) or superlative (Q1817208) for comparable adjectives; just use positive (Q3482678) for others.\n...\n- Lexicographical Coverage in Russian based on Leipzig Corpora Collection\n\n- Forms in Wikidata: 915,556\n- Forms in Wikipedia: 651,825\n- Tokens: 290,067,562\n- Covered forms: 141,451 (21.7%)\n- Missing forms: 510,374 (78.3%)\n- Covered tokens: 193,900,523 (66.8%)\n- Missing tokens: 96,167,039 (33.2%)\n- Most frequent missing forms\n\n---\n\nTitle: tomato - Wiktionary, the free dictionary\nURL: https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/tomato\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nSee also: tom\n...\ntōmato, and tōm̧ato\n...\ntomato (countable and uncountable, plural tomatoes)\n...\n- Arama\n...\n:ܛܵܡܵܛ\n...\nܐ m (ṭamaṭa)\n...\n- Asturian: tomate(ast) m\n- Azerbaijani: pomidor(az)\n- Bashkir:помидор(pomidor)\n- Bulgarian:домат(bg) m (domat)\n- Catalan: tomaquera f\n- Chechen:бадаржан стом(badaržan stom)\n- Chinese: Cantonese:番茄(faan1 ke4-2) Mandarin:西紅柿/西红柿(zh)(xīhóngshì),番茄(zh)(fānqié),柿子(zh)(shìzi) (dialectal)\n...\n- Crimean Tatar: pamidor\n- Czech:\n...\n(cs)\n...\n- Danish: